```
In this example, the multi-line comment at the beginning describes the purpose and functionality of the following if-then-else statement. The commented out line within the if statement (processData();) is being temporarily disabled without having to remove it entirely from the script. Meanwhile, the single-line block comment before the else block explains what that specific section of code does (sending an email with an error message).

