Comments are used in OpenROAD Actian 4GL programming language (2.0) for several purposes:

1. To explain the logic and purpose of specific lines of code or sections of a script, making it easier for other developers to understand the codebase. For example, if you have a complex algorithm, comments can help clarify its workings.

```
// This function calculates the average salary of all employees in the department
function avg_salary(department)
begin
  declare total as decimal;
  declare count as integer;

  // Loop through all employees in the specified department
  for each employee in select * from employees where department = :department do
    // Increment the count of employees processed
    incr(count);

    // Add up the total salary of each employee
    total += employee.salary;
  end loop;

  // Return the average salary as a decimal value
  return total / count;
end;
```

