Using block comments in OpenROAD can be helpful when you want to provide detailed explanations, notes, or documentation for a section of code. This is particularly useful for long, complex sections of code where it might be difficult for other developers to understand what the code does and why certain decisions were made. Block comments can also help you keep track of your own thoughts and ideas as you are writing and testing code, making it easier to go back and make changes or improve the code later. Here's an example scenario:
```
/*
** This block comment explains the purpose of a function that calculates the average salary for all employees in the database. It includes notes on the assumptions made and any potential limitations or edge cases.
*/
